    "For algebraic deductions, AlphaGeometry cannot flesh out its intermediate derivations, which is implicitly carried out by Gaussian elimination, therefore leading to low readability.",
    "Overall, this comparison points to the use of higher-level tools to improve the synthetic data, proof search and readability of AlphaGeometry.",
    "Note that in the original IMO 2004 P1, the point P is proven to be between B and C. The generalized version needs further contraints on the position of O to satisfy this betweenness requirement.",
